I don't know how many others will run into this, but wanted to put this out in case it helps someone since I know doing a test query to verify the shop is installed is common to do in apps, I just didn't take into account how scope changes would affect my implementation of it

After looking into it I found the real cause:

I have a check on my server that verifies the shop actually has the app installed by running a test query.

This is useful in case of a missed webhook which would cause my DB to not accurately reflect the install status of a shop
